```mermaid
graph TD
    A[Project Initiation] --> B[Planning and Definition]
    B --> C[Design and Development]
    C --> D[Process Validation]
    D --> E[Production and Delivery]
    E --> F[Project Closure]

    A --> A1[Receive RFQ]
    A1 --> A2[Gather Customer Requirements]
    A2 --> A3[Conduct Feasibility Analysis]
    A3 --> A4[Develop Initial Project Plan]
    A4 --> A5[Provide Technical Inputs and Cost Estimation]
    A5 --> A6[Submit Quote]
    A6 --> A7[Allocate Project to PM]

    B --> B1[Conduct Kick-off Meeting]
    B1 --> B2[Define Project Scope, Objectives, and Deliverables]
    B2 --> B3[Develop Detailed Project Plans]
    B3 --> B4[Create Bill of Materials (BOM)]
    B4 --> B5[Prepare Requirement Development Sheet and Sign-off]
    B5 --> B6[Appoint Team Members and Secure Resources]

    C --> C1[Design Injection Moulds, Jigs, Fixtures]
    C1 --> C2[Conduct Technical Reviews and Approvals]
    C2 --> C3[Develop Prototype Parts]
    C3 --> C4[Conduct Initial Trials and Technical Try-outs]
    C4 --> C5[Validate Design through Trials and Testing]

    D --> D1[Conduct Process Validation Trials]
    D1 --> D2[Establish Process Capability (Initial MSP)]
    D2 --> D3[Prepare Quality Proving Documents]
    D3 --> D4[Conduct Initial Process Capability Studies]
    D4 --> D5[Submit PPAP and PSW for Customer Approval]

    E --> E1[Begin Production as per Validated Process]
    E1 --> E2[Monitor Production and Address Issues]
    E2 --> E3[Track Delivery Schedules]
    E3 --> E4[Ensure Timely Delivery to Customer]
    E4 --> E5[Conduct Final Gate Reviews]
    E5 --> E6[Obtain Final Sign-off from Customer]

    F --> F1[Conduct Final Project Review Meeting]
    F1 --> F2[Document Lessons Learned and Best Practices]
    F2 --> F3[Archive Project Documents and Reports]
    F3 --> F4[Conduct Team Debrief]
    F4 --> F5[Recognize and Reward Team Members]
